* Use egen or egen_go to generate a maximally planar graph with no vertices of 
  degree < 5 using the expansion method described in

    C. Morgenstern and H. Shapiro. 1991.
    Heuristics for Rapidly Four-Coloring Large Planar Graphs.
    Algorithmica, 6, 869-891.

* Stdin to egen should contain, in order, 
  (1) the initial circuit size (roughly 1/3 the size of the desired graph),
  (2) a random number stream seed, and
  (3) the name of a file in which to dump the graph edges in DIMACS format.

* Stdout from egen includes generation stats and the "p" field of the
  DIMACS coloring format.  

* Run egen_go to produce a complete DIMACS formatted map file (read
  egen_go for usage).  Egen_go invokes egen and combines stdout with the
  edge file.

* Tested with gcc on a SPARCstation-2 running 4.1.1.  

* I'd like to hear of any problems (or ideas!) you have using
  this generator.

			Craig Morgenstern
			Department of Computer Science
			Texas Christian University
			Fort Worth, Texas, 76129
			(817) 370-2372
			morgenst@riogrande.cs.tcu.edu


